Facts about ME!
.
1️⃣ I was born a twin at birth, the twin didn’t make it & lead me to be born only (3LBS) pre-mature in order to survive the birth.
2️⃣ I grew up very shy & introverted. Thankfully sports & fitness helped me break out of the shell. I still have many moments of my shyness & introverted-ness, but let’s just say it’s nothing like it use to be.
3️⃣ My P.E. (Physical Education) 9th Grade class-we had Co-ED team sports. We probably played about 50+ games & I was so competitive I made sure I won just about all the games except I went 49-1 lol... I lost the last game of the year in Hockey (the championship) so I guess moral of the story is yes I was competitive lol.
4️⃣ I used to hate onions, mushrooms, & coconut-now athey are three of the things I love now a days. I’m sure many of us can relate to taste bud changes since we were little till now though.
5️⃣ I had trained for 9-10 years before I ever stepped on the NPC competitive stage. I guess for me back then & even now as you noticed in 9th grade I never enjoyed losing. So the reason I loved the gym (not competing) was cuz it was just always me vs me & just a stress reliever growing up. Once I got into competing & took 10th my first show (I had no idea what I was doing)! Which lead me continue till I became a winner & I did 4 shows into it and won my class & took overall. Then I was hooked cuz we only play the sports we are good at usually.... right 😂😂
6️⃣ Where I’m at today I owe it to my first leap of faith quitting my dry-wall construction job & pursuing my personal training venture out of my own garage back in the day - after a while I going at that. I had about 40-45 clients a day from 1on1 + Group. Then my social media started to take off with everything & I slowly transitioned into online which allowed me to not be training clients from what seemed like 8am - 10/11pm at night at one point. But also, I am able to help change many more lives. Never anticipated the transition but super thankful that’s for sure🙏🏼
.

ONE of the ways to become your best self...
.
“PURSUE YOUR DREAMS!”
.
Start by ask yourself - what is your ultimate dream; the thing you want more than anything? What is your true calling in life?
.
These are some of the important questions to ask yourself in order to unlock who you are meant to be.
.
Pursuing your dreams will give you determination to see your goals through, and will spark your creativity and inspiration.
.
Plus, you will be doing something that makes you happy and holds your interest.

For many, the hardest part is identifying the goals you want to pursue. You may need to explore different opportunities to see what sticks and what doesn’t.
.
You may want to focus on a problem that you want to solve or an issue you’re enthusiastic about. Remember, your goals and ambitions can change and morph over time - and that’s okay!
.
The only rule you should heed is that your dreams must come from within yourself - they shouldn’t be a reflection of what others want for you or what you think you should be doing.
.
If you’re pursuing something solely for the sake of a good income, or to live up to someone else’s expectations, you will fall short.
.
.

Your personal life, your professional life, and your creative life are all intertwined.
.
I went through a few very difficult years where I felt like a complete failure. But it was actually really important for me to go through that.
.
Struggle, for me, is the most inspirational thing in the world at the end of the day - as long as you treat it that way.
.
Again we all want success & happiness! And to each of us that may look very different but in the end I feel it’s all really the same just depends on who you are talking to!
.
So in the process of becoming who we want to be, it’s all a similar road of learning to love yourself in the highs and lows of it!
.
Because yes it won’t be as Rocky once said “SUNSHINE AND RAINBOWS” no, not at all!
.
Learn to be mentally tough and always take a lesson from the struggles along the way, and remember to be grateful of highs or “good times” because it won’t always be that way!
.
Thank you for reading my thoughts and message today! If you enjoyed this post please leave a comment and feed back below... Much love #MrWycked 🙏🏼😈

The STRONGEST factor of success is self-esteem: .
YES THAT RIGHT!
.
....believing you can do it, believing you deserve it, and believing you will get it.
.
Once you have mastered your own self belief, you’ll start to see things naturally fall into place.
.
However I say that like it’s so easy... it’s not! It’s certainly not as most of us have what we call “self-doubt” that kicks in daily and that we don’t deserve these things we want in life.
.
It’s never that we don’t deserve what we want in life.. only that we don’t deserve what we haven’t simply worked for.
.
So if on the daily you tally enough WINS, yes things you have on your to-do list, BIG or small, it doesn’t matter! Just start placing things on your list to help you achieve those DAILY WINS helping you creep towards those goals!
.
Week after week as you start to win you’ll start to build what we call momentum, and once that momentum compounds on itself you get more and more self belief.. that YES, I CAN DO THIS!
.
That self-doubt slowly leaves and all you know about yourself is Self Confidence 🔥
.
That’s when I said earlier things fall Into place!
.
So guess what-tomorrow is Monday people. That’s right pick (5) things tomorrow you want/need to get accomplished & and start your week off with a WIN!
.
No one to blame but ourselves for a loss! But that won’t be us, that’s right. We starting tomorrow off with a W - let’s go!
.

#TBT to my Pro-Debut at the Governors Cup in Sacramento, CA!
.
I was 200-201lbs on stage that day, for those who will ask (lol because you guys always do)
.
Do I miss the stage not so much.
Do I miss the overall process.. YES!
.
The difference between the two THE STAGE vs THE PROCESS.
.
To me.... “THE STAGE” is the place where the champion is crowned after many weeks - months of hard work & preparation!
.
Yes this is true, but is the best physique always crowned that day, NO! Thats because the stage is much more then just the “Best Physique” it’s a combination of many things but mostly when out on that stage it’s...your presentation to showcase your strengths & hiding any weaknesses you may have.
.
Which is a hard skill to master - as in the art of posing and to have flow to it.. again many men & woman can look phenomenal in the gym but not many can piece that together on the actual stage as that is truly an art!!
.
For me simply loving the gym as just a place to build myself up, the posing/flexing wasn’t ever my thing. As I never had a desire at a early age to really compete, rather just lifted because it made me feel good & more confident.
.
The reason I personally love “THE PROCESS” more vs the stage.
.
Because in the process of the PREP we learn so much more about ourselves as in the sacrifice, the discipline, the hard-work, the commitment, the challenge, the mindset, the overall transformation of self improvement!
.
It’s the process that makes us better, from the lessons along the way cuz you will be challenged beyond what you normally would do any given day.. why?!
.
Well because yes it’s a competition, it’s something that will have you digging deeper than just going through the motions.
.
So do I miss the stage - Not so much. But do I miss the prep process Yes. Will I ever get back out on that stage again... we’ll see where life takes me.
.
Do I personally still enjoy prepping my own Wycked Comp Athletes & my Lifestyle Clients! 100% wouldn’t change that for the world I love all of them! They give me purpose & they give me a reason to wake up daily - thank you Fam! But my return still TBD!
.
